\frac{-1}{1+t^2} e^{-At} (t  \sin(A) + \cos(A)) \leq  e^{-At}
A,t \in \mathbb{R}_{+}
e^{-At}
t,A
g(t)=\left(t+\frac{\sin A}2\right)^2+1+\cos A-\frac{\sin^2A}4\geqslant 1+\cos A-\frac{\sin^2A}4
g(t)=t^2+t\sin A+1+\cos A\geqslant 0.
1+\cos A-\frac{\sin^2A}4=\frac 14\left((2+\cos A)^2-1\right)\geqslant 0,
e^{-At}>0
(1+t^2)>0
 -t \sin(A)-\cos(A) \leq 1+t^2 
 |t \sin(A) + \cos(A)| \leq 1+t^2 . 
|t\sin A+\cos A|≤\sqrt{1+t^2}
x>1
